---
// Org Policies interactive — bulletproof contrast, security-team scenario
---

<div class="op-widget" data-op-widget>
  <svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 680 380" role="img">
    <title>Organization policies in the GCP hierarchy</title>
    <desc>Three policy guardrails attached to the Organization node, flowing down to all folders, projects, and resources below.</desc>
    <defs>
      <marker id="op-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M2 1L8 5L2 9" fill="none" stroke="context-stroke" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <g class="op-node" data-policy="building" style="cursor:pointer">
      <rect x="80" y="20" width="520" height="64" rx="10" fill="#FBEAF0" stroke="#993556" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="340" y="46" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-weight="500" font-size="14" fill="#621D38">Organization</text>
      <text x="340" y="66" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="12" fill="#993556">The whole city — yourcompany.com — where zoning laws attach</text>
    </g>

    <g class="op-policy" data-policy="public-buckets" style="cursor:pointer">
      <rect x="40" y="110" width="180" height="80" rx="8" fill="#FAEEDA" stroke="#854F0B" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="130" y="135" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-weight="500" font-size="13" fill="#633806">🚫 No public buckets</text>
      <text x="130" y="158" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#854F0B">storage.publicAccess</text>
      <text x="130" y="174" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#854F0B">Prevention</text>
    </g>

    <g class="op-policy" data-policy="region-lock" style="cursor:pointer">
      <rect x="250" y="110" width="180" height="80" rx="8" fill="#E1F5EE" stroke="#0F6E56" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="340" y="135" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-weight="500" font-size="13" fill="#085041">🌍 Region lock</text>
      <text x="340" y="158" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#0F6E56">resourceLocations</text>
      <text x="340" y="174" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#0F6E56">Data residency</text>
    </g>

    <g class="op-policy" data-policy="external-iam" style="cursor:pointer">
      <rect x="460" y="110" width="180" height="80" rx="8" fill="#E6F1FB" stroke="#185FA5" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="550" y="135" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-weight="500" font-size="13" fill="#0C447C">🔒 Domain-only IAM</text>
      <text x="550" y="158" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#185FA5">allowedPolicyMembers</text>
      <text x="550" y="174" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#185FA5">Identity boundary</text>
    </g>

    <line x1="130" y1="195" x2="130" y2="220" stroke="#888" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/>
    <line x1="340" y1="195" x2="340" y2="220" stroke="#888" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/>
    <line x1="550" y1="195" x2="550" y2="220" stroke="#888" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/>
    <line x1="130" y1="220" x2="550" y2="220" stroke="#888" stroke-width="0.5"/>
    <line x1="340" y1="220" x2="340" y2="245" stroke="#888" stroke-width="0.5" marker-end="url(#op-arrow)"/>

    <g>
      <rect x="80" y="252" width="520" height="50" rx="8" fill="#2c2a26" stroke="#4a4a48" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="340" y="270" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#f0eee6">Every folder, project, and resource below</text>
      <text x="340" y="288" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#b4b2a9">Policies inherit downward — even Owners cannot violate them</text>
    </g>

    <g>
      <rect x="80" y="320" width="520" height="50" rx="8" fill="#3c2820" stroke="#854F0B" stroke-width="0.5"/>
      <text x="340" y="338" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#efad4e">The architect's "why"</text>
      <text x="340" y="356" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="central" font-size="11" fill="#d3d1c7">Trust the architecture, not the engineers' good intentions</text>
    </g>
  </svg>

  <div class="op-detail-panel" data-op-panel>
    <div class="op-prompt">
      <span class="op-prompt-icon">→</span>
      <span>Click any policy above to read what it does and when you'd use it</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="op-quiz">
    <div class="op-quiz-header">
      <span class="op-quiz-tag">Quick check</span>
      <span class="op-quiz-meta">Your security team is terrified</span>
    </div>
    <p class="op-quiz-q">Your security team won't sleep. They're worried about three things at once:</p>
    <ul class="op-quiz-list">
      <li>A developer accidentally making a Cloud Storage bucket <strong>public</strong> and leaking customer data</li>
      <li>Customer data ending up <strong>outside the EU</strong> (GDPR violation)</li>
      <li>An engineer granting access to a <strong>personal Gmail account</strong> for "convenience"</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="op-quiz-q-bottom">Pick the org policies that would technically prevent each of these — not just discourage them.</p>

    <div class="op-quiz-options" data-op-options>
      <button data-policy="public-buckets">🚫 Block public Cloud Storage buckets</button>
      <button data-policy="region-lock">🌍 Restrict resource locations to EU regions only</button>
      <button data-policy="external-iam">🔒 Allow only @yourcompany.com identities</button>
      <button data-policy="vm-external-ip">🌐 Block VMs from getting external IPs</button>
      <button data-policy="sa-key-creation">🔑 Disable service account key creation</button>
      <button data-policy="none">⛔ None — trust our engineers to do the right thing</button>
    </div>

    <button class="op-check-btn" data-op-check>Check my policy set</button>

    <div class="op-quiz-feedback" data-op-feedback></div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDivElement>('[data-op-widget]').forEach((root) => {
    const policyData: Record<string, { title: string; accent: string; body: string }> = {
      building: {
        title: "Organization — where the zoning laws live",
        accent: "#e88aab",
        body: "Org policies attach at the Organization node and inherit downward to every folder, project, and resource. Unlike IAM (which says <em>who can do what</em>), org policies say <em>what is allowed to exist at all</em> — regardless of who's asking. They're the technical equivalent of city zoning laws: not a permission grant to a specific person, but a hard constraint baked into the architecture itself."
      },
      "public-buckets": {
        title: "🚫 No public buckets — storage.publicAccessPrevention",
        accent: "#efad4e",
        body: "When set to <code>enforced</code>, no Cloud Storage bucket in the entire org can be made public. Even an Owner with full IAM rights cannot toggle <code>allUsers</code> access. This is the single most important policy for any company handling customer data — and the most common audit finding when missing. <strong>The pattern: deny dangerous things at the org level, then carve out specific exceptions only at folders that genuinely need them.</strong>"
      },
      "region-lock": {
        title: "🌍 Region lock — gcp.resourceLocations",
        accent: "#5dcaa5",
        body: "Restricts where resources can be created — EU-only for GDPR, India-only for RBI data localization, US-only for FedRAMP. Without it, a developer in your Bangalore office can spin up Cloud SQL holding regulated EU customer data in <code>us-central1</code> by accident, and you've just become a GDPR violation. With the policy set, the API rejects the request before the resource exists."
      },
      "external-iam": {
        title: "🔒 Domain-only IAM — iam.allowedPolicyMemberDomains",
        accent: "#7eb6f0",
        body: "Restricts IAM bindings to identities from your own organization's domain. Without it, an engineer can grant <code>Owner</code> on a project to <code>random-consultant@gmail.com</code>. With it, only <code>@yourcompany.com</code> identities can ever appear in IAM bindings anywhere. For Fortune 500 clients, this is non-negotiable — the kind of thing that gets immediately flagged in a SOC 2 audit if missing."
      }
    };

    const panel = root.querySelector<HTMLDivElement>('[data-op-panel]')!;

    root.querySelectorAll<SVGGElement>('.op-node, .op-policy').forEach((node) => {
      node.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const key = node.dataset.policy!;
        const data = policyData[key];
        if (!data) return;
        panel.innerHTML = `
          <div class="op-detail-title" style="color: ${data.accent};">${data.title}</div>
          <p class="op-detail-body">${data.body}</p>
        `;
        panel.style.borderColor = data.accent;
      });
    });

    const selected = new Set<string>();
    const optionsEl = root.querySelector<HTMLDivElement>('[data-op-options]')!;
    optionsEl.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('button').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const key = btn.dataset.policy!;
        if (key === 'none') {
          selected.clear();
          optionsEl.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('button').forEach(b => {
            b.style.background = '';
            b.style.borderColor = '';
            b.style.color = '';
          });
          selected.add('none');
          btn.style.background = '#3a1818';
          btn.style.borderColor = '#e08585';
          btn.style.color = '#e08585';
          return;
        }
        const noneBtn = optionsEl.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-policy="none"]')!;
        noneBtn.style.background = '';
        noneBtn.style.borderColor = '';
        noneBtn.style.color = '';
        selected.delete('none');

        if (selected.has(key)) {
          selected.delete(key);
          btn.style.background = '';
          btn.style.borderColor = '';
          btn.style.color = '';
        } else {
          selected.add(key);
          btn.style.background = 'var(--color-info-bg)';
          btn.style.borderColor = 'var(--color-info)';
          btn.style.color = 'var(--color-info)';
        }
      });
    });

    const fb = root.querySelector<HTMLDivElement>('[data-op-feedback]')!;
    root.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-op-check]')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
      fb.style.display = 'block';

      if (selected.has('none') || selected.size === 0) {
        fb.className = 'op-quiz-feedback warning';
        fb.innerHTML = '<strong>Your security team can\'t sleep — and they\'re right.</strong> "Trust our engineers" is not a control; it\'s a hope. The whole point of org policies is that engineers <em>cannot</em> violate them, even when they\'re tired, in a hurry, or genuinely don\'t know better. Pick the three policies that map to each fear and try again.';
        return;
      }

      const must = ['public-buckets', 'region-lock', 'external-iam'];
      const missing = must.filter(p => !selected.has(p));
      const bonus = ['vm-external-ip', 'sa-key-creation'].filter(p => selected.has(p));

      if (missing.length === 0) {
        fb.className = 'op-quiz-feedback success';
        let msg = '<strong>✓ Your security team can sleep tonight.</strong> Public buckets blocked → no accidental data leak. Region locked to EU → no GDPR violation. Domain-only IAM → no rogue Gmail accounts. Each fear maps to a constraint, and each constraint is now a hard wall, not a hopeful guideline.';
        if (bonus.length > 0) {
          msg += ` <strong>Bonus credit</strong> for ${bonus.length === 2 ? 'both' : 'the'} additional ${bonus.length === 1 ? 'policy' : 'policies'}: `;
          if (selected.has('vm-external-ip')) msg += 'blocking external IPs on VMs eliminates a huge attack surface (forces all internet traffic through a NAT or load balancer where you can log it). ';
          if (selected.has('sa-key-creation')) msg += 'disabling service account key creation forces workload identity instead — the #1 source of GCP credential leaks on GitHub goes away entirely. ';
          msg += 'You\'re thinking like a real architect: build the controls into the platform, not the people.';
        } else {
          msg += ' Two bonus policies you could add: blocking VM external IPs (forces NAT/load-balancer-only egress) and disabling service account key creation (kills the #1 source of credential leaks on GitHub).';
        }
        fb.innerHTML = msg;
      } else {
        fb.className = 'op-quiz-feedback warning';
        let hint = '<strong>Close — but at least one fear isn\'t covered yet.</strong><ul>';
        if (missing.includes('public-buckets')) hint += '<li>Without <strong>blocking public buckets</strong>: the first fear (data leak via accidental public bucket) is still possible. One developer toggling <code>allUsers</code> and you\'re in the headlines.</li>';
        if (missing.includes('region-lock')) hint += '<li>Without <strong>region lock</strong>: the second fear (data leaving the EU) is still possible. One <code>us-central1</code> typo and you have a GDPR breach to report.</li>';
        if (missing.includes('external-iam')) hint += '<li>Without <strong>domain-only IAM</strong>: the third fear (Gmail account in IAM bindings) is still possible. SOC 2 will flag this in the first 10 minutes of audit.</li>';
        hint += '</ul>';
        fb.innerHTML = hint;
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  .op-widget { margin: 2rem 0; }
  .op-node:hover rect, .op-policy:hover rect { filter: brightness(0.97); }
  .op-detail-panel {
    background: #2c2a26;
    border: 1px solid #4a4a48;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    min-height: 100px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .op-prompt {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    color: #b4b2a9;
    font-size: 14px;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  .op-prompt-icon {
    color: #efad4e;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .op-detail-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .op-detail-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
    color: #f0eee6;
  }
  .op-detail-body strong { color: #ffffff; font-weight: 500; }
  .op-detail-body em { color: #d3d1c7; font-style: italic; }
  .op-detail-body code {
    background: #1a1815;
    color: #efad4e;
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
  .op-quiz {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .op-quiz-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .op-quiz-tag {
    background: var(--color-info-bg);
    color: var(--color-info);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .op-quiz-meta { font-size: 13px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); }
  .op-quiz-q { font-size: 15px; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .op-quiz-list {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    padding-left: 20px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .op-quiz-q-bottom { font-size: 14px; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .op-quiz-options {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .op-quiz-options button {
    font-size: 13px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .op-check-btn { width: 100%; padding: 10px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; }
  .op-quiz-feedback {
    display: none;
    padding: 12px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .op-quiz-feedback.success { background: var(--color-success-bg); color: var(--color-success); }
  .op-quiz-feedback.warning { background: var(--color-warning-bg); color: var(--color-warning); }
  .op-quiz-feedback ul { margin: 8px 0 0; padding-left: 20px; }
  .op-quiz-feedback li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .op-quiz-feedback code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
</style>
